response: "{ \"title\": \"Egg Carton Filler\", \"description\": \"Imagine you have an egg carton with 12 empty compartments. You want to fill this carton with eggs, but you don't want any compartment to be empty or contain more than 3 eggs. Write a function `fill_carton` that takes the number of eggs as input and returns whether it's possible to fill the carton according to the rules.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef fill_carton(n: int) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): The total number of eggs you have.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if it's possible to fill the carton, `False` otherwise.\\n\", \"code\": \"def fill_carton(n: int) -> bool:\\n    # Check if the number of eggs is less than 12\\n    if n < 12:\\n        return True\\n    # Calculate the maximum number of eggs that can be placed in each compartment\\n    max_eggs_per_compartment = (n - 1) // 3 + 1\\n    # Check if the carton can be filled with this many eggs per compartment\\n    return n % (max_eggs_per_compartment * 4) == 0 and max_eggs_per_compartment <= 3\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert fill_carton(12) == True\", \"assert fill_carton(13) == False\", \"assert fill_carton(25) == True\", \"assert fill_carton(100) == False\"] }"
